        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): prevent silent misparse of multi-colon delivery targets",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nBoth suffix parsers in `parseTelegramTarget` had the same silent-misparse bug for multi-colon targets:\n\nBefore fix:\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"chatId:topic:42:99\\\")` → `{ chatId: \\\"chatId:topic:42\\\", messageThreadId: 99 }` ← `:topic:42` residue in chatId\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"a:b:topic:42\\\")` → `{ chatId: \\\"a:b:topic\\\", messageThreadId: 42 }` ← wrong chatId\n\n**Fix:** Extract a shared `hasOversplitColons` guard and apply it to both parsers:\n- **Topic parser** (`^(.+?):topic:(\\\\d+)$`): non-greedy `.` so `t.me/mychannel:topic:9` correctly captures `t.me/mychannel`. Guard rejects chatIds with unexpected colons not part of a known t.me URL form.\n- **Colon parser** (`^(.+):(\\\\d+)$`): same guard — greedy `.` preserves `https://t.me/mychannel:9`; guard catches `chatId:topic:42:99`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n```\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  PR #97823 v3 — Topic + colon guard, t.me topic-form\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n── Multi-colon misparse → full-string fallback ──\n  ✅ 1. chatId:topic:42:99 rejected\n  ✅ 2. a:b:topic:42 rejected\n  ✅ 3. deeply nested rejected\n\n── t.me URL-form: legacy :N suffix ──\n  ✅ 4. scheme-less t.me\n  ✅ 5. full https URL\n\n── t.me URL-form: explicit :topic:N suffix ──\n  ✅ 6. scheme-less :topic:\n  ✅ 7. https :topic:\n\n── Regression: valid formats unchanged ──\n  ✅ 8. plain numeric\n  ✅ 9. @username\n  ✅ 10. chatId:topic:N\n  ✅ 11. chatId:N\n  ✅ 12. prefix stripping\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  12 passed, 0 failed\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n```\n\n### Tests\n```bash\n$ pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  46 passed (46)\n```\n\n## Tests and validation\n- `pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts` — 46 passed\n- `npx oxlint` — no lint issues\n- Changes: 2 files, +44 -18\n\n## Risk checklist\n- [x] **User-facing behavior change**: No. Valid formats unchanged.\n- [x] **Backward compatible**: 100%. All t.me URL forms (`t.me/...:N`, `t.me/...:topic:N`, `https://t.me/...:N`, `https://t.me/...:topic:N`) preserved.\n- [x] **Plugin SDK surface change**: No.\n- [x] **New dependency**: No.\n- [x] **Both parsers guarded with shared invariant**: Yes (`hasOversplitColons`).",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-target-multiple-colon-misparse",
